metadata.name: Ripples #27
metadata.description:
Ripples - Made by Zoltan Szalay @insgraphizm with P5.js
April 2022, Hungary

Features
--------

Light or Dark background
Number of rings
Detail of noise

Keyboard control
----------------
[f] toggle fullscreen and hide cursor
[space] manually generate new composition
[a] automatically generate new composition
[s] save image

Touchscreen
-----------
Tap left edge to automatically or right edge to manually generate a new composition.

metadata.name: hollow #99
metadata.description:
In 1993, Basque sculptor Eduardo Chillida proposed a project to create an immense void inside Tindaya, the Sacred Mountain of Fuerteventura's indigenous inhabitants. The hollow cube measuring approximately 45 x 50 x 65 meters was conceived as a space for "all the people" to "fully experience the tininess of humankind".

The idea of the project dates back to the 1980s, and it took the artist years of searching for the ideal mountain in different parts of the world. However, what was ideal for Chillida evoked a lot of controversy due to the environmental and social impact of the project. There was uncertainty about Tindaya's structural feasibility and the potential harm to the ancient petroglyphs engraved on its surface. What's more, the financial sustainability of the project's economic model would depend on hundreds of thousands of tourists visiting the site each year, converting a work of art into a holiday attraction.

Chillida called his project the Monument to Tolerance. Although it never came into existence, it has caused division and conflict since it was conceived.


"hollow" is an exploration of 256 voids in nonexistent natural monuments. Made of digital matter instead of stone and lacking cultural charge, its sole purpose is to contemplate the tininess of humankind.


-----

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the quality from preview to the resolution of a print of approximately 30cm in height. In live mode, click on PNG to save the rendered image.

Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes from a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones to render the image. 

Requirements: 1GB of RAM. The system needs up to 200 MB of free RAM for rendering square preview images and up to 400 MB of free RAM for rendering square images at the highest resolution. I tested on Chrome, Safari, Firefox, Edge / Windows, Mac OS, Android, and iPhone, but please make sure it works on your device before minting.

-----

Possible features:

color scheme: cairngorm, alborz, bardenas, atlas, bieszczady, watkins

proportions: square, wide, standard, narrow

frame: none, vignette, bright, dark, bright with vignette, dark with vignette

visitors: tourists, tourists and birds, solitary flock of birds, only light

metadata.name: Plottable Fibers #81
metadata.description:
More info: https://greweb.me/plots/465

Spring season is here! Plottable Fibers explore the beauty of Perlin noise simulating the behaviour of sprouting in Nature. There are many combination of parameters at stake: different intensity of noises, different width and elevation, different inks,...

The digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art: Owning this NFT confers the right to request a physical plot (A4) – this is an optional decoupling as you can already enjoy the digital version:
- The digital representation simulates fountain pen drawing on paper. art published via a digital NFT on Tezos.
- Utility token to the physical world: Right Click Save to get the SVG recipe. using @greweb's services at https://greweb.me/plots/nft but also for any artist to interprete it with their own materials.

@greweb – 2022 – tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM – CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #388
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.name: In the woods : natural edition. #35
metadata.description:
Project born after an inspirational walk in the woods.

This project includes different features depending on the style of the display, the size of the elements, the colors… some items are rare…

In Open Live window, press « p » to pause the building process, press « s » to save the current image.
To get a High Resolution Image : press « r » to change the resolution for high definition, the image will reload and you can then use « s » to save the image.

Visit https://sites.google.com/view/tidally-disrupted-star/ for  both genesis description of the project and an overview of the minting possibilities…

metadata.name: Humanoid #31
metadata.description:
Humanoids are breathing creatures that will help you calm down if you sync your breathing with them. 
Each humanoid will use 1 of 3 meditative breathing patterns that will actually relax you, go on, test it!

This project evolved out of the results I saw in Aquarium. Humanoids are my interpretation of a generative pfp project.
I'm playing with shapes and colors to see what interesting compositions occur and to see when a combination of shapes becomes more.
The backgounds change color, shifting through every color once every hour.

I hope you enjoy your Humanoid as much as I did creating them.

Press [p] to pause and play.
Press [s] to open the settings screen.

Features:
Black and white
Breathing pattern
Desaturated
Facing direction
Hollow
Neon
Outline
Type

metadata.name: Punkasso #70
metadata.description:
Punkassos
---------
A pfp collection inspired by global events and the painting "Guernica" by Pablo Picasso.
We need to move beyond war and learn to talk to each other once again.
We need to work together locally and globally to thwart authoritarian regimes that wish to destabilize and send us back 100 years.
Never forget.
Remember the repressed from the past and help those who suffer today and will suffer in the future.
Say no to fascism, genocide, slavery, repression and suppression.
Say no to lies and propaganda.
Say no to the wealthy who wish to keep using you as a pawn.

metadata.name: Countdown #184
metadata.description:
80% of the benefits from primary sales will go to the nonprofit "One Earth", check out their mission and their projects in www.oneearth.org

---------------

We need your help! The Earth is melting!

"Countdown" is a project that tries to show some consequences of global warming and pollution. It does so by representing a glacier that will melt over time, acting as a Countdown for our time left to react to the Climate Crisis.

If you visit this token every other day, the melting will start to be noticeable, and around one year, most of the ice will be gone. The token will also show signs of pollution: the sky colors will desaturate, stars will be less visible on night palettes, and the ice and water will get dirtier. Lastly, the penguin families will start disappearing, as the ice melts and they lose their home.

All the information of the token is available on the browser's console (Features + Token evolution).

---------------
- 365 editions, as the ice will melt almost completely in one year
- 13 color palettes, with different rarities
- 3 ice shades
- Different number of penguin families
---------------

Press "s" to save a 2000x2000px png with the current state of the token

metadata.name: The Arcimboldo Project #29
metadata.description:
A tribute to Giuseppe Arcimboldo (1526 - 1593), an Italian painter best known for creating imaginative portrait heads made entirely of objects such as fruits, vegetables and flowers.

This token is made of a combination of 192 layers (24 layers x 8 fruits/vegetables/flowers categories).
All the layers have been hand-painted in acrylics on paper and digitally composed.
The background has a random HSV color.

As always a big thank you goes to Koei Ural - @KoeiUral for the huge help with the p5.js code!

metadata.name: Farbteiler #500
metadata.description: Each Farbteiler is a rectilinear, mostly self-avoiding walk, dividing the space of the canvas with dotted grids using colors from Johannes Itten's Farbkreis. Everything is inside and everything is outside.
